text: Ordered two set as breakfast - fried noodles, 1 meat and 1 vegetable. $8 for total means $4 per pack. I did wonder was I over charged.. yet again.. it’s never easy to earn money.. so much effort.. the meat looks like leftover ones though loll me still buy……..limited meat choices in the morning..
Authentic local coffee shop in the midst of Singaporean public housing. Pretty crowded for a shop hidden right inside a small road.
Tried the zi char stall-  the sweet and sour fish and the gong bao chicken rice set, love the food! It is delicious and tasty , as well reasonable price
Food from the zhi char stall is good & reasonably priced.
